Stability Audit Report
Generated: 2026-03-01T18:54:26Z
Repository: egohygiene/signal
Auditor: copilot
Scope: Pre-local-build stability review — frontend (ui/) and backend (server/)

================================================================================
🔴 CRITICAL — Must fix before local run
================================================================================

[C1] POST /api/plaid/transactions does not validate empty access_token
  - server/main.py:286–292: the GET /api/transactions endpoint rejects blank
    access_token (line 192–195); the POST endpoint has no equivalent guard.
  - Empty token is forwarded to Plaid, producing an opaque upstream error
    instead of a 400. Add the same blank-token check to the POST handler.

[C2] Plaid pagination not implemented — large accounts silently truncated
  - server/plaid_adapter.py:127: `transactions_get` returns at most 500 items
    per call. No pagination loop exists. Accounts with >500 transactions in the
    requested range return only the first page with no warning to the caller.
  - Affects data integrity for any real Plaid connection. Implement cursor-based
    pagination or document the hard limit in the response.

[C3] enableMocking() rejection is unhandled — app silently fails to boot
  - ui/src/main.tsx:16: `enableMocking().then(...)` has no `.catch()`.
    If the dynamic import of msw/browser throws (e.g. missing service-worker
    file), the app never renders and there is no error surfaced to the user.
  - Add a `.catch(console.error)` or explicit error handler.

================================================================================
🟡 RISK — Should fix soon
================================================================================

[R1] TransactionsList shows "No transactions found" before sync completes
  - ui/src/features/transactions/TransactionsList.tsx:10: reads directly from
    Zustand store. The DataSyncProvider populates the store after query data
    arrives. During that window the store is empty, causing a false-negative
    empty state before loading finishes.
  - Pass an isLoading prop or read from the query directly in this component.

[R2] isInMonth silently drops transactions on malformed date strings
  - ui/src/utils/transactionUtils.ts:12–14: `new Date(dateStr)` returns
    `Invalid Date` for non-ISO strings. `getUTCFullYear()` on an Invalid Date
    returns NaN, so the guard fails silently and those transactions are excluded
    from every monthly total without any log or error.
  - Add a date-format assertion and log a warning on invalid input.

[R3] normalize_transaction silently defaults critical IDs to empty string
  - server/plaid_adapter.py:177–178: when `transaction_id` or `account_id` is
    absent from the raw dict, `tx.get("transaction_id", "")` produces an empty
    string that satisfies the Pydantic model. Downstream deduplication and
    account-level grouping will be silently corrupted.
  - Raise an exception (or at minimum log a warning) when these required IDs
    are absent rather than defaulting to empty string.

[R4] DataSyncProvider error useEffect fires on every mount with null errors
  - ui/src/providers/DataSyncProvider.tsx:56–65: the effect iterates all four
    query errors on every mount, including the initial state where all errors
    are null. The `if (err)` guard prevents spurious log output today, but if
    the guard is ever removed or restructured this will produce false error logs.
  - Restructure to only log errors that are non-null, and consider not running
    the effect when no errors exist.

[R5] Global faker.seed() in FakeDataProvider mutates shared module instance
  - ui/src/providers/FakeDataProvider.ts:121–123: `faker.seed(SEED)` modifies
    the global faker singleton. If multiple test files import this module in
    parallel, seed state leaks between tests, producing non-deterministic output.
  - Use `new Faker({ locale: [en] })` with an explicit seed instead of seeding
    the global instance.

================================================================================
🔵 IMPROVEMENT — Can defer
================================================================================

[I1] POST body exposes access_token — prefer header transport
  - server/main.py:124–130: `TransactionsRequest` places `access_token` in the
    JSON request body. The GET endpoint correctly uses an X-Access-Token header
    to keep tokens out of logs. Align the POST endpoint for consistency.

[I2] No gcTime configured on QueryClient — implicit 5-minute default
  - ui/src/query/queryClient.ts:3–11: `staleTime` is set explicitly but
    `gcTime` (formerly `cacheTime`) is not. The TanStack Query v5 default is
    5 minutes, which is acceptable but should be explicit to avoid surprises
    when upgrading.

[I3] usePoolSummary / useBudgetSummary: new Date() outside useMemo
  - ui/src/features/pools/usePoolSummary.ts:22–24 and
    ui/src/features/budgets/useBudgetSummary.ts:18–20: `new Date()` is called
    on every render before `resolvedYear`/`resolvedMonth` are computed. This
    is not inside the `useMemo` callback, so the Date is constructed on every
    render even when the memo result is reused. Move inside useMemo or
    memoize separately.

[I4] TransactionSchema date field accepts any string — no format constraint
  - ui/src/schema/v1/transaction.ts:9: `date: z.string()` does not enforce
    YYYY-MM-DD format. A malformed date from the API passes Zod validation and
    then silently fails the isInMonth filter (see R2).
  - Add `z.string().regex(/^\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}$/)` to enforce format at the
    boundary.

[I5] Non-null assertion on root DOM element has no graceful fallback
  - ui/src/main.tsx:18: `document.getElementById('root')!` will throw a
    cryptic TypeError if the element is absent (e.g. template change). Add a
    null check with a descriptive error message.

[I6] Server transaction log loop iterates up to 10 sensitive records
  - server/main.py:329–345: the POST endpoint logs the first 10 transaction
    names and merchant names to stdout. In a non-sandbox environment this
    leaks real financial merchant names to server logs.
  - Gate this detailed logging behind `settings.debug` or remove in production.

